decision_conditions:
Condition : 1 - The existing public footpath, together with the connection
    to Lithos Road, shall be retained permanently for use by
    the public and any changes to the routing of the footpath
    shall be approved by the Council before any re-routing
    takes place.

Condition : 2 - Details of traffic calming measures which shall be
    constructed to department of Transport standards shall be
    submitted for approval by the Council and provided within
    six months os approval.

Condition : 3 - The whole of the parking accommodation shown on the
    drawings shall be provided and retained permanently for the
    parking of vehicles of the occupiers and users of the
    remainder of the building.

Condition : 4 - To safeguard the amenities of the adjoining premises and
    the area generally.
Condition : 5 - In the interests of highway safety and residential amenity.

Condition : 6 - To ensure the permanent retention of the accommodation for
    parking purposes and to ensure that the use of the building
    does not add to traffic congestion.
